        <p>US 20190082043</p>
        <p>User interface system comprising voice to electronic signal subsystem</p>
        <p>US 20190082043 User interface system comprising voice to electronic signal subsystem: Embodiments of the invention provide a communication system including a processor; and a memory coupled to the processor. The memory may include a communication module with an Interactive Voice Response (IVR) system that is configured to communicate with a user. The IVR system may include a voice-to-electronic signal subsystem, a processing subsystem, and an output subsystem. The voice-to-electronic signal subsystem may be configured to receive a user's voice input and convert it to an electronic signal for further processing. The processing subsystem may be configured to analyze the electronic signal and determine an appropriate response from a database. The output subsystem may be configured to communicate the appropriate response back to the user through a speaker, display, or other communication channel.</p>
